                  </hi>. I am assistant to Charles Wilson, a woollen<lb></lb>draper, on Ludgate-street. I received some information about half-past eleven o'clock, on the 10th of Oct., and found the prisoner with this piece of cloth, belonging to my master—I had seen it a day or two before inside the lobby—I know it by a private mark—it goes by the name of doeskin—the prisoner said he was very badly off, and merely took it to be transported, he wished to be transported.</p>
